> Chicken carnitas are better than all other kinds of chicken. Yep, we're talking
> seared pieces of white meat simmered in a Fajita-spiced tomato sauce with a
> tangle of charred onion and poblano. Everything is then piled into steamy flour
> tortillas along with pickled onion, tomato scallion salsa, and chipotle lime
> crema. One bite and your taste buds will be immediately transported south of
> the border. Taco' bout a weeknight win!

Wash and dry all produce. Halve and peel @red onion{1}; finely chop one half and
very thinly slice other. Core, deseed, and finely chop @poblano pepper{1}. Finely
dice @Roma tomato{1}. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}. Quarter @lime{1}.

In a #small microwave-safe bowl{}, combine @white wine vinegar{5%tsp},
@sugar{1%tsp}, a large pinch of @salt{}, and @water{1%tbsp}; stir to dissolve.
Stir in sliced onion. Microwave for ~{30%seconds}; set aside to quick-pickle,
stirring occasionally.

Pat @chicken breast strips{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{}. Heat a drizzle of
@vegetable oil{2%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken and
season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and
cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. If
necessary, wipe out pan.

While chicken cooks, in a #small bowl{}, combine @sour cream{2%tbsp}, a squeeze
of lime juice, @chipotle powder{1/4%tsp} (taste and add more if you like things
spicy), and a pinch of salt and pepper. Add water 1 tsp at a time until mixture
reaches a drizzling consistency. In a #medium bowl{}, combine tomato, scallions,
a large squeeze of lime juice, salt, and pepper.

Heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for chicken over medium-high heat. Add
chopped onion, poblano, salt, and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, until
veggies are softened, ~{3-4%minutes}. Return chicken to pan and add
@fajita spice blend{1%tbsp}, @tomato paste{1.5%oz}, @chicken stock concentrate{1},
and @water{1/4%cup}. Cook, stirring, until saucy and slightly reduced,
~{2-3%minutes}. Turn off heat. Season with salt and pepper.

Meanwhile, wrap @flour tortillas{6} in damp paper towels and microwave until
warm and pliable, about ~{30%seconds}. Divide chicken filling, salsa, pickled
onion (draining first), and crema between tortillas. Serve with any remaining
lime wedges on the side.

> Alternatively, put everything in individual serving bowls and let everyone
> assemble their own tacos.